AES to Sell its Solar Energy Division in Spain, Expansion Says

-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 
2011-04-01T05:27:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-01/aes-to-sell-its-solar-energy-division-in-spain-expansion-says.html
AES Corp. (AES) , the U.S. power producer
with operations in more than two dozen countries, plans to sell
its solar energy power plants in Spain after power subsidies
were cut,  Expansion  said.  The company has hired  JPMorgan Chase & Co. (JPM)  to find a buyer
for its photovoltaic generators in Spain and wants more than 120
million euros ($170 million) for the assets, the newspaper said,
citing unidentified people with knowledge of the matter.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid at 
 ssmyth2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Blackman at   ablackman@bloomberg.net . 